  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PH R1: Strengthening Climate Advocacy in Asia in the time of COVID-19</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to :
-strengthen capacities for climate advocacy in the time of COVID-19 where face to face engagement are no longer the norm in the short term.
-support the work of ACCC members engaging in online advocacy through virtual roundtables, webinars and online campaigning. Specifically:
1)influencing the COVID 19 recovery/devt planning processes, the NDC and National adapt processes,  with the purpose of strengthening movement-building, policy, and campaign on climate action in the normal.  
2) providing the access to online platforms, it is the hope of ACCC that  COVID-19 programs do nor further suppress movement-building and  to further the right of CSOs and other stakeholders to participate in governance.  
3) Supporting ACCC members gain access to inter--governmental platforms, regionally, other stakeholders and multi-lateral development banks and financial instiutions
4)  ACCC will keep its commitment to the communities they work for to ensure alternative participatory and feedback mechanisms that inform the policy advocacy work.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For ACCC, within a year&apos;s time, we envision a regional civil society organization, along with its members, that is capable of ensuring the continuity of climate and disaster resilience advocacy, through innovate approaches, in government, inter-governmental, and relavant platforms in the face of  COVID 19 and the new normal.</narrative>
  </description>
